@startuml
[*] as Initial State
state "Inventory" as InventoryState
state "Adding Goods" as AddingGoodsState
state "Updating Price" as UpdatingPriceState
state "Removing Goods" as RemovingGoodsState
state "Expired Goods" as ExpiredGoodsState
state "Order Placed" as OrderPlacedState
state "Invoice Generated" as InvoiceGeneratedState
state "Searching Items" as SearchingItemsState
state "Purchase Made" as PurchaseMadeState
state "Billing Process" as BillingProcessState
state "Receipt Generated" as ReceiptGeneratedState

[*] --> InventoryState: Initial State

InventoryState -->|Add Goods|> AddingGoodsState: Add new goods to inventory
AddingGoodsState -->|Update Price|> UpdatingPriceState: Update price of existing items in inventory
UpdatingPriceState -->|Remove Goods|> RemovingGoodsState: Remove goods from inventory that are no longer required

RemovingGoodsState -->|Expired Goods|> ExpiredGoodsState: Identify expired goods and notify user about removal from inventory

InventoryState -->|Place Order|> OrderPlacedState: Place an order to supplier for additional goods when required
OrderPlacedState -->|Invoice Generated|> InvoiceGeneratedState: Generate invoice for the order once it is placed

InventoryState -->|Search Items|> SearchingItemsState: Search for items available in inventory and select them for purchase
SearchingItemsState -->|Purchase Made|> PurchaseMadeState: Calculate applicable discount and tax based on selected items

PurchaseMadeState -->|Billing Process|> BillingProcessState: Generate receipt for customer after purchase
BillingProcessState -->|Replace Item or Cancel Receipt|> InventoryState: Replace an item or cancel the receipt during billing process if needed

InventoryState -->|Record Customer Request|> InventoryState: Record customer requests for items that may not be currently available

PurchaseMadeState -->|View Summary Report|> InventoryState: View a summary report of all transactions carried out in system at any point

[*] as Final State
@enduml
